'''包装怒'''（{{lang-en|Wrap rage}}或{{lang|en|package rage}}）也称'''开箱怒'''<ref>{{cite web|author1=中国日报网|title=英语热词：收到快递后打不开时的“包装怒”|url=http://edu.qq.com/a/20141112/017529.htm|website=腾讯教育|accessdate=2017-01-02|archive-date=2017-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103012321/http://edu.qq.com/a/20141112/017529.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，指很难打开产品[[包裝|包裝]]时所带来的高水平[[憤怒|憤怒]]与[[挫折|挫折]]感，尤其常见于一些热封[[塑料|塑料]]的{{tsl|en|Blister pack|吸塑包装}}和{{tsl|en|Clamshell (container)|蛤壳}}包装。每年都有上千人受到这种状况造成的伤害，例如被工具（用来开启包装）或者包装本身划破手指或扭到手腕，并且有时还损坏了包装裡的物品。易于打开的设计可以提高打开包装的便捷性。

== 背景 ==
包装的设计方向有时必须要使其难以打开。例如，法规要求部分[[非处方药|非处方药]]必须采用[[防篡改|防篡改]]机制以防止预期客户之前的未授权开启，以及[[兒童安全包裝|兒童安全包裝]]。其他被设计为难以开启的包装是为减少{{tsl|en|Package pilferage|包装内容物偷窃}}和[[店舖盜竊|店舖盜竊]]。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bendbulletin.com/article/20110602/NEWS0107/106020402/|title=Clamshell packaging is being tossed|last=Clifford|first=Stephanie|date=2011-06-02|work={{tsl|en|The Bulletin (Bend)|The Bulletin}}|accessdate=2011-06-06|location=[[本德_(俄勒冈州)|Bend, OR]]|agency={{tsl|en|New York Times News Service}}|archive-date=2013-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005041243/http://www.bendbulletin.com/article/20110602/NEWS0107/106020402/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

硬塑料吸塑包装还可在运输时保护产品。<ref name="ABCNews">{{Cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Business/Video/playerIndex?id=2692861|title=Wrap Rage|accessdate=2009-08-03|date=2006-12-01|publisher=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|archive-date=2017-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103165232/http://abcnews.go.com/Business/Video/playerIndex?id=2692861|dead-url=no}}</ref>此外，使用透明塑料使客户得以在购买之前直观地看到产品。<ref name="Oyster07">{{Cite web|url=http://www.consumerreports.org/cro/money/shopping/shopping-tips/oyster-awards-3-07/overview/0307_oyster_ov_1.htm|title=The Oyster Awards|accessdate=2009-08-04|date=March 2007|publisher=''{{tsl|en|Consumer Reports}}''|archive-date=2010-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100325200920/http://consumerreports.org/cro/money/shopping/shopping-tips/oyster-awards-3-07/overview/0307_oyster_ov_1.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

术语“wrap rage”本身是媒体关注这一现象而产生。虽然早在1998年就已有其他变体被使用，例如“packaging rage”。{{tsl|en|Word Spy}}认为[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]最早在2003年使用“wrap rage”一词。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wordspy.com/words/wraprage.asp|title=Wrap rage|accessdate=2009-08-03|date=2005-03-01|publisher={{tsl|en|Word Spy}}|archive-date=2014-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703025103/http://www.wordspy.com/words/wraprage.asp|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Diary">{{Cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/comment/citydiary/2868234/City-diary.html|title=City diary|accessdate=2009-08-10|date=2003-11-07|last=Moore|first=James|publisher=''[[The_Daily_Telegraph_(UK)|The Daily Telegraph (UK)]]''|archive-date=2019-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190611075850/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/comment/citydiary/2868234/City-diary.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{tsl|en|American Dialect Society|美国方言学会}}认定该词语为2007年最有用的词语之一。<ref name="ADS">{{Cite web|url=http://www.americandialect.org/Word-of-the-Year_2007.pdf|title=Word of the Year 2007|accessdate=2009-08-06|date=2008-01-04|publisher={{tsl|en|American Dialect Society}}|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126023409/http://www.americandialect.org/Word-of-the-Year_2007.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 挫折与伤害 ==
2006年，《[[消费者报告|消费者报告]]》杂志为最难打开的产品包装设立了牡蛎奖（Oyster Awards），展现出包装怒现象。<ref name="Oyster07" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.consumerreports.org/cro/personal-finance/hardtoopen-packages-306/overview/index.htm|title=The Oyster Awards|accessdate=2009-08-03|date=March 2006|publisher=''Consumer Reports''|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070613044108/http://www.consumerreports.org/cro/personal-finance/hardtoopen-packages-306/overview/index.htm|archivedate=2007-06-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[匹兹堡邮报|匹兹堡邮报]]》的一则有关包装怒的故事<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/06064/665356-51.stm|title=Today's Packages Can Be Murder to Open|accessdate=2009-07-26|date=2006-03-05|last=Carpenter|first=Mackenzie|publisher=''[[Pittsburgh_Post-Gazette|Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]''|archive-date=2011-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629100633/http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/06064/665356-51.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>被[[科尔伯报告|科尔伯报告]]选中，主持人{{tsl|en|Stephen Colbert (character)|｜Stephen Colbert}}尝试用一把小刀取出塑料包装中的一个新[[计算器|计算器]]，结果无济于事。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0458254/quotes?item=qt0476231|title=Quotes|accessdate=2014-01-12|publisher=[[IMDb|IMDb]]|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304183712/http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0458254/quotes?item=qt0476231|dead-url=no}}</ref>

根据Yours杂志的一次调查，在2000名受访者中，99%表示包装在过去10年里变得愈加难开，97%的受访者说包装过剩，以及60%的受访者说他们购买了包装更易于打开的产品。<ref name="Yours">{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/3456645.stm|title='Wrap rage' hitting the over-50s|accessdate=2009-08-01|date=2004-02-04|publisher=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|archive-date=2021-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211190326/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/3456645.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>在{{le|考克斯商学院|Cox School of Business}}进行的一项调查中，接近80%的家庭对塑料包装表示“恼火、沮丧或彻底的愤怒”。<ref name="Canada">{{Cite web|url=http://www.canada.com/reginaleaderpost/news/weekender/story.html?id=4959f929-0f35-4e5c-8118-cbe90771b5f5&p=2|title=Plastic packaging angers consumers|accessdate=2009-08-10|date=2008-01-26|publisher={{tsl|en|Canada.com}}|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110140609/http://www.canada.com/reginaleaderpost/news/weekender/story.html?id=4959f929-0f35-4e5c-8118-cbe90771b5f5&p=2|archivedate=2012-11-10}}</ref>消费者在描述这些产品时也倾向于使用如“怨恨”和“困难”之类的词语。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/06/11/AR2005061100199.html|title=But the Dang Thing Won't Open|accessdate=2009-08-01|date=2005-06-12|last=Gemperlein|first=Joyce|publisher=''[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]''|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112204348/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/06/11/AR2005061100199.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

消费者有时使用潜在不安全的工具来尝试打开包装，例如[[剃刀片|剃刀片]]、[[多用途刀|多用途刀]]、{{tsl|en|Snips|剪钳}}或[[碎冰锥|碎冰锥]]。<ref name="ABCNews"/>在Yours的调查中，71%的受访者表示他们曾在打开食品包装时受伤。最常见的受访者伤害是在打开包装时：“切到手指、切到手、扭伤手腕、手瘀伤，以及[[肩|肩部]][[肌肉拉伤|肌肉拉伤]]。”<ref name="Yours"/>根据英国的一项研究，每年有超过6万人因开封食品包装受伤而接受住院治疗。<ref name="Diary" />[[美國消費品安全委員會|美國消費品安全委員會]]估计，2004年美国因尝试开启包装而导致了6,500人次的急诊室就诊。<ref name="Wenzel">{{Cite web|url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-11128_3-9912173-54.html|title=Killing the oyster pack|accessdate=2009-08-03|date=2008-04-07|last=Wenzel|first=Elsa|publisher=[[CNET|CNET]]|archive-date=2012-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102082804/http://news.cnet.com/8301-11128_3-9912173-54.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2009年由{{le|美国医学研究所|National Academy of Medicine}}进行的一项研究发现，17%的21岁以上成年人至少受伤一次或知道有人在打开节日或生日礼物时受伤。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.myfamilywellness.org/wraprage |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2009-12-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101215041821/http://www.myfamilywellness.org/wraprage |archivedate=2010-12-15 }} Avoid 'Wrap Rage' This Holiday Season, December 2009</ref>

== 解决方案 ==
[[File:Packaging_Designed_For_Humans-2.jpg|替代=带有“轻松打开标签”的脊状塑料蛤壳包装]]

=== 包装设计 ===
如果包装商和零售商愿意，有许多种解决方案可以使客户能更容易地拿取包装内的物品。但在易于拿取的同时，也容易造成更高的被盗率。

一些公司正在使他们的包装更容易被消费者打开，以帮助减少沮丧感。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://consumerist.com/346980/|title=Companies Respond To Wrap-Rage, Design Packaging That Isn't So !@$% Difficult To Open|accessdate=2009-08-03|date=2008-01-20|publisher=''{{tsl|en|The Consumerist}}''|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20110929022115/http://consumerist.com/346980/|archivedate=2011年9月29日}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=200285450|title=Amazon Certified Frustration-Free Packaging FAQs|accessdate=2012-06-02|publisher=Amazon.com|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111182413/https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html/?nodeId=200285450|dead-url=no}}</ref>其他公司则继续坚持包装的防篡改（避免开启）特性。推动改进包装的力量包括消费者、零售商以及[[老年人|老年人]]，他们发现随着年龄的增长，打开包装变得越来越困难。<ref name="TreeHugger">{{Cite web|url=http://www.treehugger.com/files/2008/02/wrapper_rage_ma.php|title=Wrapper Rage Making Consumers Crazy|accessdate=2009-08-03|date=2008-02-11|last=Alter|first=Lloyd|publisher={{tsl|en|TreeHugger}}|archive-date=2011-09-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110913054323/http://www.treehugger.com/files/2008/02/wrapper_rage_ma.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>

长期以来，已经有多种使包装容易开启的方法可用。这包括{{tsl|en|Perforation|穿孔}}、{{tsl|en|Tear tape|撕带}}和断开设计。但一些易开启的特性可能增加包装的成本。

=== 开启 ===
家用[[剪刀|剪刀]]或[[多用途刀|多用途刀]]有时被用于打开难以开启的包装。{{tsl|en|Snips|锡剪}}对有韧性的塑料有效。高级的复合金属剪刀的[[机械优势|机械优势]]使其即使用很少的手部力量也能轻松开启包装。有些包装还可以用普通的家用[[開罐器|開罐器]]开启。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.moneytalksnews.com/how-to-open-plastic-packaging-without-injuring-yourself/|title=How to Open Plastic Packaging (Without Hurting Yourself)|accessdate=2015-03-31|author=Donofrio, Craig|publisher=MoneyTalksNews|archive-date=2020-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101195459/https://www.moneytalksnews.com/how-to-open-plastic-packaging-without-injuring-yourself/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

